pageContext.claim:
“All these people for doing it from The New York Times, which is a fake newspaper -- we don't even want it in the White House anymore.
We're going to probably terminate that and The Washington Post. They're fake.”
pageContext.analysis: It's baloney when the president says he no longer reads The Washington Post or the New York Times. The White House apparently stopped getting print delivery, but Trump continues to refer to stories in both newspapers in public remarks and tweets.
